## Pre-Flight Checklist

Verify all physical prerequisites before proceeding.

- [ ] All {{ nodes | length }} nodes are racked and powered
{%- for node in nodes %}
  - [ ] {{ node.name }}: hardware installed, cabled to managed switch
{%- endfor %}
- [ ] Each node has boot NVMe and data NVMe installed
- [ ] All nodes are cabled to the managed switch
{%- if has_replication_network %}
- [ ] Point-to-point replication cables between all node pairs:
{%- for node in nodes %}
{%- if node.repl_peers is defined and node.repl_peers %}
{%- for peer_name, peer in node.repl_peers.items() %}
{%- if node.name < peer_name %}
  - [ ] {{ node.name }} ({{ peer.iface }}) ↔ {{ peer_name }}: DAC cable connected
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}
- [ ] NAS ({{ nas.hostname }}) is powered and accessible at {{ nas.ip }}
- [ ] SSH key access to NAS: `ssh {{ nas.ssh_user }}@{{ nas.ip }}` works without password
- [ ] Proxmox ISO available on USB drive
- [ ] Operator workstation can reach management subnet ({{ management.subnet }})
- [ ] Can log into domain registrar at {{ platforms.registrar.url }}
- [ ] Know how to add DNS records (NS and A) at the registrar
- [ ] Have verified existing email records (MX, SPF, DMARC) for {{ domain }}
- [ ] `age` and `sops` CLI tools installed on operator workstation
- [ ] `nix` package manager installed on operator workstation
{%- if nix_builder is defined and nix_builder.type is defined %}
{%- if nix_builder.type == 'linux-builder' %}
- [ ] macOS with Nix installed (the linux-builder VM will be set up in a later step)
- [ ] At least 8GB RAM available for the Nix linux-builder VM
{%- elif nix_builder.type == 'remote' %}
- [ ] SSH access to `{{ nix_builder.remote_host }}` as `{{ nix_builder.remote_user }}` using key `{{ nix_builder.remote_ssh_key }}`
- [ ] Remote host is running Linux (`uname -s` returns `Linux`)
{%- elif nix_builder.type == 'local' %}
- [ ] Workstation is Linux with Nix installed
{%- endif %}
{%- endif %}
